    </cit>
    <etym xml:lang="ru">По-видимому, относится к группе слов для ‘округлых’, ‘пухлых’ предметов с
        фонетическим типом %ikp(n)%i, %ikp(t)%i, %ikp(l)%i; ср. <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_g0ybyn"/> ‘живот’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_gæbæt"/> ‘бурдюк’ и др.
        (рассмотрены под словом <ref type="xr" target="#entry_tymbyl"/> ‘круглый’). Прослеживается в
        некоторых соседних и более отдаленных языках: <mentioned xml:lang="ka-x-rach"
                ><lang/><w>gobani</w></mentioned> (<bibl><ref target="#ref_Беридзе"/></bibl>),
            <mentioned xml:lang="ka"><lang/><w>gobani</w></mentioned>(%bмохев.%b) (<bibl><ref
                target="#ref_Макалатия"/><biblScope xml:lang="ru">Хеви, стр.
                149</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">Khevi, p. 149</biblScope></bibl>),
            <mentioned xml:lang="x-vaynakh"><lang/><w>guen</w><note type="comment" xml:lang="">
                ()</note><note type="comment" xml:lang="">
            ()</note><gloss><q>тюфяк</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="x-vaynakh"
                ><w>ǧaiba</w><gloss><q>подушка</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned
            xml:lang="ru-x-dial"
            ><lang/><w>кубень</w><gloss><q>толстуха</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
            xml:lang="ru-x-dial"><w/><gloss><q>толстая баба</q></gloss></mentioned>, (<bibl><ref
                target="#ref_Даль"/></bibl>).</etym>
    <etym xml:lang="en">Apparently, it is related to a group of words for ‘roundish’, ‘puffy’
        objects with a phonetic type %ikp(n)%i, %ikp(t)%i, %ikp(l)%i; compare <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_g0ybyn"/> ‘stomach’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_gæbæt"/> ‘wineskin’
        etc. (considered under the word <ref type="xr" target="#entry_tymbyl"/> ‘round’). It can be
        traced in some neighbouring and more distant languages: <mentioned xml:lang="ka-x-rach"
                ><lang/><w>gobani</w></mentioned> (<bibl><ref target="#ref_Беридзе"/></bibl>),
            <mentioned xml:lang="ka-x-mokhev"><lang/><w>gobani</w></mentioned> (<bibl><ref
                target="#ref_Макалатия"/><biblScope xml:lang="ru">Хеви, стр.
                149</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">Khevi, p. 149</biblScope></bibl>),
            <mentioned xml:lang="x-vaynakh"><lang/><w>guen</w><note type="comment" xml:lang="">
                ()</note><note type="comment" xml:lang=""> ()</note><gloss><q>straw
                mattress</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="x-vaynakh"
                    ><w>ǧaiba</w><gloss><q>pillow</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned
            xml:lang="ru-x-dial"><lang/><w>кубень</w><gloss><q>fat
            woman</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="ru-x-dial"><w/><gloss><q>stout
                    woman</q></gloss></mentioned>, (<bibl><ref target="#ref_Даль"/></bibl>).</etym>
</entry>
